lenders.name: Matt Dunbar
lenders.loan_because: Why not?  After bank fees, investment fees, and so forth, realistically one can't expect to see a no-risk return of more than 6%.  When taking likely less than a 10% loss on kiva.org, consider what you can do for others giving up 16% of your money  Sure, 16% sounds like a lot, but it really isn't.  In most cases, even living on $100/week, the difference $16 would make to you is substantially smaller to what $16 could do for others in third world countries.  $16 may mean the difference between you feeling hungry or not as a low income individual, but $16 in some countries where money is sent can mean the difference between eating and starving to death.
